ALIGN=CENTER>The Epistle of Paul to the Ephesians</H2></CENTER><P><A            
HREF='index.htm'>Return to Index</A>.</P><CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5  
WIDTH=90%><TR><TD></TD><TD><CENTER><H1>Chapter 1</H1></CENTER></TD></TR><TR><TD 
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD><TD><P>Paul, an apostle of YAHSHUA         
MASHIYACH by the will of ELOHIYM, to the saints which are at Ephesus, and to    
the faithful in MASHIYACH YAHSHUA:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V2>  
<H4>2</H4></TD><TD><P>Grace be to you, and peace, from ELOHIYM our Father, and  
from the ADONAY YAHSHUA MASHIYACH.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V3>  
<H4>3</H4></TD><TD><P>Blessed be the ELOHIYM and Father of our ADONAY YAHSHUA   
MASHIYACH, who hath blessed us with all spiritual blessings in heavenly places  
in MASHIYACH:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V4><H4>4</H4></TD><TD><P> 
According as he hath chosen us in him before the foundation of the world, that  
we should be holy and without blame before him in love:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD    
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD><TD><P>Having predestinated us unto the    
adoption of children by YAHSHUA MASHIYACH to himself, according to the good     
pleasure of his will,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V6><H4>6</H4></TD>
<TD><P>To the praise of the glory of his grace, wherein he hath made us         
accepted in the beloved.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V7><H4>7</H4>  
</TD><TD><P>In whom we have redemption through his blood, the forgiveness of    
sins, according to the riches of his grace;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A  
NAME=V8><H4>8</H4></TD><TD><P>Wherein he hath abounded toward us in all wisdom  
and prudence;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V9><H4>9</H4></TD><TD><P> 
Having made known unto us the mystery of his will, according to his good        
pleasure which he hath purposed in himself:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A  
NAME=V10><H4>10</H4></TD><TD><P>That in the dispensation of the fulness of      
times he might gather together in one all things in MASHIYACH, both which are   
in heaven, and which are on earth; even in him:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP>
<A NAME=V11><H4>11</H4></TD><TD><P>In whom also we have obtained an             
inheritance, being predestinated according to the purpose of him who worketh    
all things after the counsel of his own will:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP>  
<A NAME=V12><H4>12</H4></TD><TD><P>That we should be to the praise of his       
glory, who first trusted in MASHIYACH.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A       
NAME=V13><H4>13</H4></TD><TD><P>In whom ye also trusted, after that ye heard    
the word of truth, the gospel of your salvation: in whom also after that ye     
believed, ye were sealed with that holy Spirit of promise,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD 
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V14><H4>14</H4></TD><TD><P>Which is the earnest of our       
inheritance until the redemption of the purchased possession, unto the praise   
of his glory.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V15><H4>15</H4></TD><TD>  
<P>Wherefore I also, after I heard of your faith in the ADONAY YAHSHUA, and     
love unto all the saints,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V16><H4>      
16</H4></TD><TD><P>Cease not to give thanks for you, making mention of you in   
my prayers;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V17><H4>17</H4></TD><TD><P> 
That the ELOHIYM of our ADONAY YAHSHUA MASHIYACH, the Father of glory, may give 
unto you the spirit of wisdom and revelation in the knowledge of him:</P></TD>  
</TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V18><H4>18</H4></TD><TD><P>The eyes of your     
understanding being enlightened; that ye may know what is the hope of his       
calling, and what the riches of the glory of his inheritance in the saints,</P> 
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V19><H4>19</H4></TD><TD><P>And what is the 
exceeding greatness of his power to us-ward who believe, according to the       
working of his mighty power,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V20><H4>   
20</H4></TD><TD><P>Which he wrought in MASHIYACH, when he raised him from the   
dead, and set him at his own right hand in the heavenly places,</P></TD></TR>   
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V21><H4>21</H4></TD><TD><P>Far above all             
principality, and power, and might, and dominion, and every name that is named, 
not only in this world, but also in that which is to come:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD 
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V22><H4>22</H4></TD><TD><P>And hath put all things under his 
feet, and gave him to be the head over all things to the church,</P></TD></TR>  
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V23><H4>23</H4></TD><TD><P>Which is his body, the    
fulness of him that filleth all in all.</P></TD></TR></TABLE><!--This Software  
